{"metadata":{"navigatorTitle":[{"text":"TemplateRegistry","kind":"identifier"}],"fragments":[{"text":"class","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"TemplateRegistry","kind":"identifier"}],"title":"TemplateRegistry","modules":[{"name":"NodeKit"}],"roleHeading":"Class","externalID":"s:7NodeKit16TemplateRegistryC","symbolKind":"class","role":"symbol"},"schemaVersion":{"major":0,"minor":3,"patch":0},"kind":"symbol","topicSections":[{"generated":true,"identifiers":["doc:\/\/NodeKit\/documentation\/NodeKit\/TemplateRegistry\/init(pageSize:)"],"title":"Initializers","anchor":"Initializers"},{"generated":true,"identifiers":["doc:\/\/NodeKit\/documentation\/NodeKit\/TemplateRegistry\/loadedTemplates","doc:\/\/NodeKit\/documentation\/NodeKit\/TemplateRegistry\/pageSize","doc:\/\/NodeKit\/documentation\/NodeKit\/TemplateRegistry\/totalCount","doc:\/\/NodeKit\/documentation\/NodeKit\/TemplateRegistry\/totalPages"],"title":"Instance Properties","anchor":"Instance-Properties"},{"generated":true,"identifiers":["doc:\/\/NodeKit\/documentation\/NodeKit\/TemplateRegistry\/itemCount(inPageAt:)","doc:\/\/NodeKit\/documentation\/NodeKit\/TemplateRegistry\/register(template:)","doc:\/\/NodeKit\/documentation\/NodeKit\/TemplateRegistry\/registeredNodeTemplate(with:)","doc:\/\/NodeKit\/documentation\/NodeKit\/TemplateRegistry\/unregister(templateKindID:)"],"title":"Instance Methods","anchor":"Instance-Methods"}],"seeAlsoSections":[{"generated":true,"identifiers":["doc:\/\/NodeKit\/documentation\/NodeKit\/PortTypeRegistry","doc:\/\/NodeKit\/documentation\/NodeKit\/PortEditorRegistry"],"title":"Registries","anchor":"Registries"}],"variants":[{"paths":["\/documentation\/nodekit\/templateregistry"],"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}]}],"relationshipsSections":[{"type":"conformsTo","kind":"relationships","identifiers":["doc:\/\/NodeKit\/11Observation10ObservableP","doc:\/\/NodeKit\/s8CopyableP","doc:\/\/NodeKit\/s9EscapableP","doc:\/\/NodeKit\/s8SendableP","doc:\/\/NodeKit\/s16SendableMetatypeP"],"title":"Conforms To"}],"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"declarations","declarations":[{"languages":["swift"],"tokens":[{"text":"@","kind":"attribute"},{"preciseIdentifier":"s:ScM","text":"MainActor","kind":"attribute"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"kind":"keyword","text":"class"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"TemplateRegistry","kind":"identifier"}],"platforms":["macOS"]}]},{"kind":"mentions","mentions":["doc:\/\/NodeKit\/documentation\/NodeKit\/GettingStarted"]},{"content":[{"type":"heading","text":"Behavior when the displayed pages change","anchor":"Behavior-when-the-displayed-pages-change","level":2},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"register"},{"type":"text","text":" \/ "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"unregister"},{"type":"text","text":" re-derive the ordering under the most recent"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"predicate and re-project every loaded page onto the new snapshot"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"("},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"refreshLoadedPagesAfterMutation"},{"type":"text","text":"). Both "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/NodeKit\/documentation\/NodeKit\/TemplateRegistry\/totalCount","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" and"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/NodeKit\/documentation\/NodeKit\/TemplateRegistry\/loadedTemplates","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" are "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"@Observable"},{"type":"text","text":", so any SwiftUI view that reads them"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"re-renders automatically — there is no separate “something changed” signal"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"to subscribe to. "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"ForEach"},{"type":"text","text":" keys each cell by "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"kind.id"},{"type":"text","text":", so cells that"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"shifted position move, new ones fade in, removed ones fade out."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Page indices are positional, not durable: if a template registers that"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"sorts before the visible window, “page 5” now contains different items."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"The view shows whatever is at the current visual position rather than"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"trying to track a content anchor — a future improvement could pin a"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"scroll-anchor "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"kind.id"},{"type":"text","text":" and restore its visual position after mutations."}]},{"type":"heading","text":"Concurrency and ordering","anchor":"Concurrency-and-ordering","level":2},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The registry is "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"@Observable"},{"type":"text","text":" and isolated to "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"@MainActor"},{"type":"text","text":". "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"register"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"and "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"unregister"},{"type":"text","text":" are synchronous and, called from MainActor code, take"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"effect in call order — a synchronous loop produces deterministic,"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"sequential state."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Called from outside MainActor they need to be treated as asynchronous"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"(the call hops across actor isolation). If you issue registrations from"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"multiple async tasks, the MainActor schedules them but doesn’t order"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"them by call site — await each call before issuing the next if you"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"need a specific sequence."}]},{"type":"heading","text":"Path to a remote-backed registry","anchor":"Path-to-a-remote-backed-registry","level":2},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Today everything lives in memory. To back this with a remote source:"}]},{"type":"orderedList","items":[{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"inlineContent":[{"code":"loadTemplates(matching:pages:)","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" becomes a real I\/O call."}],"type":"strong"},{"text":" The single","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"code":"await Task.yield()","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" is the seam — replace with the actual fetch and","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"respect ","type":"text"},{"code":"Task.isCancelled","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" so fast scrolling doesn’t queue wasted work.","type":"text"}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Switch from offset to cursor pagination."}],"type":"strong"},{"text":" Offset paging is cheap in","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"memory but expensive server-side (count + skip). Each ","type":"text"},{"code":"Page","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" would gain","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"code":"nextCursor","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":"\/","type":"text"},{"code":"previousCursor","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":", and the load API keys off cursors instead","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"of integer page indices.","type":"text"}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"inlineContent":[{"code":"totalCount","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" may be unknown or approximate."}],"type":"strong"},{"text":" Large remote stores","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"often won’t report exact totals. The view then can’t compute","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"code":"totalPages","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" upfront — switch to a “has-more” flag and append a sentinel","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"placeholder section that’s swapped for real content as it loads.","type":"text"}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"inlineContent":[{"code":"register","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" \/ "},{"code":"unregister","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" likely retire."}],"type":"strong"},{"text":" Local registration only","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"makes sense for tests or in-process plugins; with a server source the","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"canonical list lives upstream.","type":"text"}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Multi-source coalescing."}],"type":"strong"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"code":"TemplatePredicate.Scope.Store","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" already","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"enumerates ","type":"text"},{"code":"project","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" \/ ","type":"text"},{"code":"installed","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" \/ ","type":"text"},{"code":"global","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" — each is a separate","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"paginated source. The registry merges them into one ordering at load","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"time, holding per-source cursors. This is the “expensive but"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"unavoidable” coalescing cost."}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"text":"Server-side filtering.","type":"text"}]},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"TemplatePredicate"},{"type":"text","text":" should be sent as a"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"query parameter so we don’t transfer non-matching items. Requires a"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"wire format (currently the enum is "},{"t